1.Why Subquery:-  step-1 Join Tables (sub query) ==> step-2 Filtering  (sub query) ==> step-3 Transformation (Sub Query)
==> Step-4 Aggregation(Main Query)
Outer query <== Inner query or Main Query <== (sub query -1<==subquery-2<==subquery-3 <==......)

2. subquery categories:-  

Dependency
i. Non-Correlated subquery: subquery is independent on main query.
ii. correlated subquery: subquery is dependent on main query. 

Result type:-
i. Scalar subquery: return only 1 value
ii. Row subquery: return multiple rows
iii. Table Subquery: returns multiple rows and columns

Location clause:-
i. SELECT
ii. FROM
iii. JOIN
iv. WHERE  1. Comparsion operators i.e., <,>,=,!=,>=,<= 2. Logical operators i.e., IN,ANY,ALL,EXISTS

3. Subquery Result Types:- 

i. Scalar subquery :- returns only single value result. ex:- SELECT AVG(sales) FROM sales.orders
ii. row subquery :- returns multiple rows & single column ex:- SELECT CUSTOMERID FROM sales.orders
iii. table subquery:- returns multiple rows & multiple columns ex:-  SELECT CUSTOMERID,sales FROM sales.orders

4. subquery in FROM clause :- Used as temporary table for the main query
syntax:- SELECT column1,column2.... FROM ( SELECT column FROM table1 WHERE condition) AS alias

--Find the products that have a price higher than the average price of all products
--Main query
SELECT 
*
FROM
	(
	--subquery
	SELECT
	ProductID,
	Price,
	AVG(PRICE) OVER () Avgprice
	FROM Sales.Products
	)T
WHERE Price > Avgprice

SELECT
*,
RANK() OVER( ORDER BY Sumsales DESC) CUSTO_RANK
FROM
(
SELECT
CustomerID,
SUM(sales) Sumsales
FROM Sales.Orders
GROUP BY CustomerID
)T

--Rank customers based on their total amount of sales
SELECT
CustomerID,
SUM(sales),
RANK() OVER(ORDER BY SUM(sales) DESC)
FROM Sales.Orders
GROUP BY CustomerID

5. How DB executes subquery
Database Engine retrives subquery query result set from DISKSPACE->USER and stores in CACHE ==>Main query is executed on 
subquery result set.

6. subquery in SELECT clause 
Note:- only scalar subquery is allowed.
syntax:- 

SELECT
columns1,
(SELECT column FROM table1 WHERE condition) AS alias --result should be scalar i.e., only 1 value
FROM table1

--show the Productids,productnames and total number of orders
SELECT
ProductID,
product,
price,
(SELECT COUNT(*)  FROM Sales.Orders) totalorders

FROM
Sales.Products

7. subquery in JOIN clause ==> used to prepare the data(filtering & aggregation) before joining it with other table.

--show all customer details and find the total order of each customer
--Main query
SELECT
c.*,
T.totalorders
FROM sales.Customers c
LEFT JOIN 
(
--subquery
SELECT 
customerid,
count(*) totalorders
FROM Sales.Orders
GROUP BY CustomerID
)T
ON c.CustomerID = T.CustomerID

8. Subquery in WHERE clause

comparsion operators :- =,<>,!=,>,>=,<,<= Always used with Scarlar subquery.
Syntax:- 
SELECT column1,column2..... 
FROM table1 
WHERE column = (SELECT column FROM table2 WHERE condition)

--Find the products that have a prie higher than the average price of all products
--Main query
SELECT
productid,
price
FROM Sales.Products
WHERE Price > (SELECT AVG(price) FROM Sales.Products)  --subquery

Logical operator IN :-  subquery returns multiple rows and single column.

--Show the details of orders made by customers in Germay
--Main Query
SELECT * FROM Sales.Orders
WHERE CustomerID IN (
--sub query
SELECT CustomerID FROM Sales.Customers WHERE Country='Germany')

ANY/ALL Operator :- ANY :- Must satisfy any of the value in the list. ALL :- Must satisfy all the value in the list.

